\cf0 Primary Key: EmployeeID\
Parent Tables: None\
What does a record represent: One employee \
who works at Northwind Traders and handles orders\
Valuable columns: EmployeeID, FirstName, \
LastName, Title, City, Country\
Calculations possible: Count orders per employee,\
sales performance per employee\
\
=== ORDERS ===\
Primary Key: OrderID\
Parent Tables: Customers, Employees, Shippers\
What does a record represent: One order placed \
by a customer handled by an employee\
Valuable columns: OrderID, CustomerID, \
EmployeeID, OrderDate, ShipCountry, ShipCity\
Calculations possible: Count orders by date,\
orders per customer, orders per employee,\
shipping time calculation\
\
=== ORDER DETAILS ===\
Primary Key: OrderID + ProductID together\
Parent Tables: Orders, Products\
What does a record represent: One product \
line item inside an order \'97 what was bought,\
how many, and at what price\
Valuable columns: OrderID, ProductID, \
UnitPrice, Quantity, Discount\
Calculations possible: Total revenue per order,\
revenue per product, discount analysis\
\
=== PRODUCTS ===\
Primary Key: ProductID\
Parent Tables: Categories, Suppliers\
What does a record represent: One product \
sold by Northwind Traders\
Valuable columns: ProductID, ProductName, \
CategoryID, SupplierID, UnitPrice, \
UnitsInStock, Discontinued\
Calculations possible: Total products per category,\
average price per category, stock levels,\
discontinued vs active products\
\
=== SHIPPERS ===\
Primary Key: ShipperID\
Parent Tables: None\
What does a record represent: One shipping \
company that delivers orders for Northwind\
Valuable columns: ShipperID, CompanyName, Phone\
Calculations possible: Count orders per shipper,\
compare shipping companies performance\
\
=== SUPPLIERS ===\
Primary Key: SupplierID\
Parent Tables: None\
What does a record represent: One company \
that supplies products to Northwind Traders\
Valuable columns: SupplierID, CompanyName,\
ContactName, City, Country, Phone\
Calculations possible: Count products per supplier,\
suppliers by country, revenue per supplier\
\
=== REGION ===\
Primary Key: RegionID\
Parent Tables: None\
What does a record represent: One geographic \
region like Eastern, Western, Northern, Southern\
Valuable columns: RegionID, RegionDescription\
Calculations possible: Sales by region,\
employees per region\
\
=== TERRITORIES ===\
Primary Key: TerritoryID\
Parent Tables: Region\
What does a record represent: One sales territory \
that belongs to a region\
Valuable columns: TerritoryID, \
TerritoryDescription, RegionID\
Calculations possible: Count territories per region,\
sales per territory\
\
=== EMPLOYEE TERRITORIES ===\
Primary Key: EmployeeID + TerritoryID together\
Parent Tables: Employees, Territories\
What does a record represent: Which territories \
each employee is responsible for\
Valuable columns: EmployeeID, TerritoryID\
Calculations possible: Count territories per employee,\
employees per territory}